  "title": "M&E Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>· Lead and oversee all M&amp;E engineering activities in construction projects, ensuring adherence to design specifications, approved drawings, and project timelines.</p>\n<p>· Manage the planning, scheduling, coordination, and integration of M&amp;E systems installation and commissioning.</p>\n<p>· Supervise M&amp;E subcontractors and vendors, ensuring quality work, safety, and compliance with contractual obligations.</p>\n<p>· Monitor and track the progress of M&amp;E works, providing regular updates to senior management and stakeholders.</p>\n<p>· Coordinate with architects, engineers, project managers, and other departments to resolve technical issues, discrepancies, and ensure seamless integration of M&amp;E systems with other building components.</p>\n<p>· Ensure compliance with regulatory standards, building codes, and quality assurance requirements (e.g., CONQUAS, QM).</p>\n<p>· Liaise with clients, consultants, relevant authorities, and subcontractors regarding M&amp;E issues, ensuring effective communication and problem resolution.</p>\n<p>· Ensure M&amp;E works comply with Safe Work Procedures and safety regulations throughout the installation and commissioning process.</p>\n<p>· Prepare and submit M&amp;E-related documentation, reports, and progress updates as required by the project schedule.</p>\n<p>· Handle any other ad-hoc duties or tasks as assigned by management.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>· Diploma/Degree in Mechanical &amp; Electrical Engineering or related fields</p>\n<p>· Minimum 4 years of relevant experience in the construction industry, with strong M&amp;E project management expertise and at least one completed project cycle.</p>\n<p>·Proficient in Autodesk Revit, BIM software, or other M&amp;E design tools·</p>\n<p><br></p>",
